{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give NHS patients a right to a second opinion",
        "additional_details": "At present NHS patients do not have a right to a second opinion, which we believe can have serious adverse consequences for patients and their family.\r\n\r\nWhere a second opinion has been requested, no further action should be taken until this has been provided.\r\n",
        "background": "Make it a law that all NHS hospitals and clinics have to give patients the option of a second opinion, and make a referral accordingly at your request.",
